## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID (resolved through the list endpoint; there is no GET-single for ACLs). |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Errors if zero or more than one ACL matches. |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | ACL integer ID. |
| `name` | ACL name. |
| `description` | ACL description. |
| `enabled` | Whether the ACL is enabled. |
| `patterns` | Ordered list of `{pattern, type}` objects (order is significant). |
| `is_builtin` | Whether this is a built-in ACL. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

### `patterns[].type` values

| type | meaning |
|---|---|
| `glob` | Shell-style glob match (the default). |
| `regex` | Regular-expression match. |
